# No Pass-Through Wrappers (Java)

Do not add a class whose public API only forwards to another type. Prefer putting behavior on the owner, caller, or an existing type that already has a reason to exist.

## Iron Law

A new type needs **non-trivial policy, state, or a real seam** (I/O, async, test double, mode routing). If removing the type and inlining one call site does not hurt clarity or testing, do not create it.

## Reject

- One-line facades (`prefetch()` → `Dungeon.prefetch…()`)
- Service locators that only `new` a composite and hold a static
- Config layers that only re-expose another config’s getters
- “Helper” classes whose every method is `return Other.method(…)`
- Existence-check APIs that re-run the same lookup the caller must do next (double fetch)

## Prefer

| Instead of                                   | Do                                                                |
| -------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Prefetch facade                              | Call the owner (`Dungeon`, storage, client) from the scene/caller |
| Online “service” factory                     | Static `echoLookup()` / `instance()` on the real lookup type      |
| Tiny health/JSON helper used once            | Private/package method on the client                              |
| Settings wrapping Env                        | One settings/config type                                          |
| `shouldX` that duplicates `resolveX` filters | One resolve path; callers use the result                          |

## Allowed thin types

- **Real routing / policy** (e.g. ranked vs local lookup)
- **Async / lifecycle** (executor, probe cache, upload queue)
- **Testable seams** (HTTP transport interface + impl)
- **Shared multi-caller API** used by several levels/UI with more than a one-liner
- **Value objects** (results, policies, DTOs)

## Before adding a class

1. Name the **extra behavior** in one sentence. If you cannot, inline.
2. Count call sites: one site → private method on the caller/owner.
3. Check for a second lookup of the same data in the same flow — collapse to one.
4. Prefer extending an existing owner over a new `*Service` / `*Helper` / `*Prefetch` type.

## Examples (echo cull)

```text
❌ EchoBossPrefetch.prefetch(depth) → Dungeon.prefetchEchoBossForDepth(depth)
✅ InterlevelScene calls Dungeon directly

❌ EchoOnlineService.echoLookup() only builds CompositeEchoLookup
✅ CompositeEchoLookup.echoLookup() owns the singleton

❌ shouldUseEchoBoss(lookup) then resolveEcho(lookup)  // two fetches
✅ prepareEchoBoss → resolveEcho once
```
